22:18.128 --> 22:19.118
What?

22:25.928 --> 22:28.170
Hey, Josh. Josh.

22:28.264 --> 22:31.007
Hey, I wanna quickly show you
something while Megan's out.

22:31.100 --> 22:32.432
Yeah, sure, buddy.

22:37.773 --> 22:41.016
<i>Here's a little secret</i>
<i>for the producers of the show.</i>

22:42.319 --> 22:43.605
What is this, man?

22:43.696 --> 22:45.858
<i>You should choose us is because</i>

22:45.948 --> 22:51.194
<i>I plan to propose to my future wife,</i>
<i>Megan, on the show.</i>

22:51.287 --> 22:53.244
<i>She doesn't know anything about it.</i>

22:55.249 --> 22:57.457
This is... this is for real?

22:57.543 --> 22:59.830
Yeah, dude, look at the ring.

22:59.920 --> 23:02.253
<i>I already got her a ring.</i>

23:02.339 --> 23:04.797
<i>I plan to...</i>

23:04.884 --> 23:07.752
Whatever happens,
Megan can't find out about this, okay?

23:07.845 --> 23:10.679
She almost came in here at
the end and ruined the surprise.

23:13.767 --> 23:16.054
Wow, man, I can't believe it.

23:16.145 --> 23:18.137
Oh, that's right, it kept recording.

23:20.649 --> 23:22.481
Hey, Jeff, Jeff.

23:25.070 --> 23:26.186
Thank you, man.

23:26.280 --> 23:28.237
Wow, so you've been thinking
about this a while?

23:28.324 --> 23:31.408
I've been thinking about it probably
the last four months or something,

23:31.493 --> 23:34.907
and after the three year anniversary
I just thought,

23:34.997 --> 23:38.035
you know, that was so perfect and why wait.

23:38.125 --> 23:40.833
And I wanted to tell you
about it first, so...

23:40.920 --> 23:44.084
Well, dude, I'm glad you did.
I'm happy for you, man.

23:44.173 --> 23:45.709
It's great.

23:45.799 --> 23:47.916
But with the video, if you don't mind,

23:48.010 --> 23:50.627
editing it and putting it
into the audition tape.

23:50.721 --> 23:53.088
Oh, yeah. Hey, Jeff, Jeff, Jeff.

23:53.182 --> 23:54.593
Don't worry about that now, dude.

23:54.683 --> 23:56.299
We'll figure it out, but let's...

23:56.393 --> 23:58.476
let's go get a drink or something.
Let's celebrate.

23:58.562 --> 24:00.019
You're getting married, man.

24:00.105 --> 24:03.849
Don't fuckin' high five me. Love you, dude.

24:03.943 --> 24:06.026
All right, let's do it. Your shout?

24:06.111 --> 24:07.318
Yeah, obviously.

24:07.404 --> 24:09.066
Oh, wait, I just forgot the camera.

24:09.156 --> 24:11.113
Oh, yeah, buddy, I got it.

24:15.120 --> 24:17.282
The dawn of a new day.

24:19.541 --> 24:21.203
That's where we're headed.

24:21.293 --> 24:25.037
Yeah, I watched all the footage.

24:30.928 --> 24:35.343
No, I don't know if we... it's the right
thing to show it, or whatever.

24:35.432 --> 24:38.425
Josh... kept filming.

24:39.561 --> 24:42.099
Hey, hey. Shark Cage Dive?

24:42.189 --> 24:43.225
Yup.

24:47.736 --> 24:50.194
Look at that. There it is.

24:51.740 --> 24:53.777
My name's on the list, yo.

24:53.867 --> 24:56.325
- My name's on the list.
- VIP list.

24:56.412 --> 24:58.495
Yeah, spelt my name wrong, but that's okay.

24:58.580 --> 25:01.448
Hey, it's such a good day. And there it is.

25:01.542 --> 25:04.626
I have, like, excited
butterflies in my tummy.

25:04.712 --> 25:06.954
My name's Andrew.
I'll be your skipper for the day.

25:20.853 --> 25:23.220
Go down together, like in the <i>Titanic.</i>

25:23.313 --> 25:26.351
And blow on this whistle hard enough,

25:26.442 --> 25:28.559
apparently the sharks will run away as well.

25:31.572 --> 25:33.985
No turning back now, boys.

25:38.620 --> 25:40.282
The skipper.

25:53.135 --> 25:54.296
<i>The ocean is beautiful.</i>

25:54.386 --> 25:55.627
Come here, check this out.

25:55.721 --> 25:56.882
<i>And meant to be enjoyed by everyone.</i>

25:56.972 --> 26:01.592
<i>The chances of dying from a shark attack</i>
<i>are just one in 900 million</i>

26:01.685 --> 26:02.846
- <i>anywhere in the world.</i>
- Wow, I didn't know that.

26:02.936 --> 26:06.805
<i>However, on rare occasions,</i>
<i>shark attacks have happened.</i>

26:06.899 --> 26:10.893
<i>There are a few things you can do</i>
<i>to avoid an unlikely encounter.</i>

26:11.904 --> 26:13.691
<i>Splashing and thrashing.</i>

26:13.781 --> 26:17.525
<i>Sharks are attracted to</i>
<i>erratic movement in the water</i>

26:17.618 --> 26:20.986
<i>as it replicates</i>
<i>the signal of distressed fish.</i>

26:22.706 --> 26:26.074
<i>Don't swim at dawn, dusk or night.</i>

26:26.168 --> 26:29.627
<i>These are the typical hunting times</i>
<i>for most species of shark.</i>

26:29.713 --> 26:31.079
Well, let's not do that then.

26:32.216 --> 26:33.923
<i>Avoid swimming alone.</i>

26:34.009 --> 26:38.253
<i>If you're swimming with other people,</i>
<i>don't separate far from the group.</i>

26:38.347 --> 26:42.261
<i>Sharks are more likely to</i>
<i>attack solitary individuals.</i>

26:42.351 --> 26:46.095
<i>Sharks can sense blood from.25 miles away.</i>

26:46.188 --> 26:51.400
Okay, so this is Josh,
and he is signing away his life.

26:51.485 --> 26:54.523
Okay, so... "entering and exiting the water,

26:54.613 --> 26:56.946
and shark cage with
a possible presence of sharks..."

26:57.032 --> 26:59.115
Hopefully, that's why we're here.

26:59.201 --> 27:01.284
"...which are unpredictable and dangerous

27:01.370 --> 27:04.738
exposing me to attack,
which may result in injury or death."

27:04.832 --> 27:09.167
Right, but there's, like, a huge great cage.

27:09.253 --> 27:10.664
I can see it from here.

27:10.754 --> 27:13.121
I think, you know what, I think
we're going to be all right.

27:13.215 --> 27:15.047
- I think we're going to be okay.
- Yeah.

27:17.386 --> 27:19.503
What the hell is that?

27:19.596 --> 27:21.303
Would a great white fit through that?

27:22.391 --> 27:24.303
Well, if it can fit through that,

27:24.393 --> 27:26.555
I don't think we got nothing to worry about.

27:32.484 --> 27:35.602
- This is the fun part, right?
- Yup.

27:35.696 --> 27:37.733
Did you know that...

27:37.823 --> 27:39.109
Yeah...

27:41.577 --> 27:43.785
I don't see anything yet.

27:43.871 --> 27:46.158
Huge one on the other side, man.

27:46.248 --> 27:48.410
- There is a huge one.
- Right now?

27:50.043 --> 27:52.160
Oh, my gosh.

27:52.254 --> 27:55.918
Oh, my gosh. Oh, wow.

27:59.428 --> 28:01.385
We're going to need a bigger boat.

28:03.974 --> 28:07.138
All right, guys, in the event
you do something really silly

28:07.227 --> 28:08.388
and fall out the cage,

28:08.478 --> 28:11.346
there's a couple of things
you gotta remember.

28:11.440 --> 28:14.982
So, basically, if you happen to do that,
you keep your two feet together,

28:15.068 --> 28:17.936
you pull the stomach wide open, okay?

28:18.030 --> 28:20.022
Feet together and these two tabs.

28:20.115 --> 28:22.903
When you pull that,
the weight belt will release, okay?

28:22.993 --> 28:24.859
And it will come straight off you like that.

28:24.953 --> 28:27.286
Who's going in first?

28:27.372 --> 28:30.160
So long, buddy.

28:30.250 --> 28:32.788
- Good luck.
- Here he comes.

28:38.550 --> 28:40.291
He was just angry...

28:41.303 --> 28:42.885
Here he comes. Look.

28:42.971 --> 28:44.758
Oh, you can see him coming.

28:44.848 --> 28:47.010
Oh, that's so scary.

28:49.561 --> 28:51.644
Hey! That was lucky.

28:51.730 --> 28:53.642
- It bumped the cage, man.
- Yup.

28:53.732 --> 28:57.191
It was just, "knock, knock, anyone in there?"

29:04.701 --> 29:05.942
She did well.

29:06.036 --> 29:08.528
Shark diving ain't for everyone.

29:08.622 --> 29:09.703
I guess not.

29:12.209 --> 29:13.996
I'm actually a bit nervous now.

29:14.086 --> 29:16.578
Take a big deep breath. Hold your nose....

29:16.672 --> 29:18.755
Breathe through that. Take a big deep breath.

29:18.840 --> 29:20.502
- I'm pumped!
- Whoo!

29:22.261 --> 29:24.503
My heart is racing.

29:25.806 --> 29:27.172
Yeah, Megan!

29:32.813 --> 29:34.645
How you going, all right?

29:34.731 --> 29:35.721
You're all right.

29:35.816 --> 29:37.227
She hasn't even seen the shark yet.

29:42.864 --> 29:44.730
Get in the water with her.

29:44.825 --> 29:45.941
- That'll do.
- Thanks.

29:46.034 --> 29:49.323
Yeah, no worries. So, do you
want me to record you going in?

29:49.413 --> 29:51.700
- It should be recording right now, brah.
- Yeah, it is.

29:53.625 --> 29:54.615
Hey, buddy.

33:08.278 --> 33:10.235
Dude, the boat's going down, you guys!

33:14.034 --> 33:16.071
Oh, my God!

33:20.290 --> 33:23.624
Are you okay? Are you okay?

33:25.962 --> 33:27.498
Are you guys okay?

33:27.589 --> 33:29.330
We're coming.

33:37.265 --> 33:39.427
There's a lot of blood.

33:39.518 --> 33:41.259
Keep his head above the water, okay?

33:43.146 --> 33:44.387
Oh, shit.

33:45.398 --> 33:48.232
Just hold it together. Apply some pressure.

33:51.488 --> 33:52.774
I'm gonna check his pulse.

33:57.285 --> 33:58.821
There's no pulse.

34:00.247 --> 34:02.330
You're going to have to
get out of his blood, okay?

34:05.669 --> 34:08.127
Get away from me! Get away!

34:09.380 --> 34:11.464
You have to get out of the blood.

34:12.759 --> 34:15.045
It's not fine. I'm bleeding everywhere.

34:15.136 --> 34:17.128
It's okay, Megan. It's only blood.

34:17.222 --> 34:18.757
Josh, can you see anything?

34:32.737 --> 34:35.605
- Oh, shit.
- Did you see that?

34:40.620 --> 34:42.110
Megan, it's all right.

34:42.205 --> 34:45.494
It's not okay! We were in a cage before!

34:45.583 --> 34:46.620
Help!

34:46.710 --> 34:48.621
It's all right, Megan. Just relax.

34:48.712 --> 34:51.079
- Oh, my God.
- Shut up for a second.

34:51.172 --> 34:52.583
- Help!
- Seriously, shut up for a second.

34:52.674 --> 34:54.710
- Quiet, quiet.
- Somebody help us!

34:54.801 --> 34:57.088
Quiet! I hear something.

35:01.057 --> 35:03.891
Hey! Hey, buddy.

35:04.978 --> 35:06.640
- What happened?
- Over here!

35:06.730 --> 35:10.895
- What happened?
- There was a freak wave.

35:10.984 --> 35:13.647
- Can you swim to us?
- We're over here!

35:25.457 --> 35:26.664
There's something in the water.

35:26.750 --> 35:27.786
What happened?

35:40.597 --> 35:42.384
Oh, shit! Megan!

35:52.984 --> 35:57.319
My name's Josh, and I'm here
with my brother, Jeff, and Megan.

35:58.323 --> 36:00.064
We're in South Australia.

36:00.158 --> 36:02.150
Our boat... Our boat sunk.

36:02.243 --> 36:03.859
I don't know how many people survived.

36:03.953 --> 36:05.160
Stop it.

36:06.164 --> 36:07.496
I don't want to hear this, okay?

36:07.582 --> 36:08.663
Just turn the camera off.

36:08.750 --> 36:12.790
In South Australia... we're waiting for help.

36:15.757 --> 36:17.749
Megan you, okay?

36:17.842 --> 36:20.129
No my leg's hurting.

36:20.220 --> 36:21.961
Can you please check?

36:22.055 --> 36:23.921
Okay, I'll have a look.

36:24.015 --> 36:26.348
Josh, keep an eye out.

36:35.318 --> 36:37.105
It's not too bad.

36:38.113 --> 36:39.820
It looks fine.

36:39.906 --> 36:42.148
I'm bleeding? Is it bleeding?

36:42.242 --> 36:43.358
It's a small cut.

36:43.451 --> 36:46.068
Oh, shit. I'm just going
to look underwater...

36:47.330 --> 36:48.537
Jeff.

36:48.623 --> 36:51.206
- Jeff, look, there's a boat, man.
- What?

36:51.292 --> 36:53.955
- Yeah, way out there.
- Where's the boat?

36:54.045 --> 36:56.537
Oh, shit. Help!

37:01.261 --> 37:02.672
I don't think they can hear us.

37:02.762 --> 37:04.128
Let's swim for it. Come on, let's go.

37:05.890 --> 37:08.473
I can't swim that far. I can't swim that far.

37:08.560 --> 37:10.017
Help!

37:10.103 --> 37:11.560
Hey, Jeff. Jeff, Jeff, Jeff.

37:11.646 --> 37:14.354
Come here, take... I'll do it.

37:16.276 --> 37:18.893
- I'm gonna go first, dude.
- What?

37:18.987 --> 37:22.321
- Jeff's gonna stay here with you.
- Wait, no, no. Josh. Josh, don't go.

37:22.407 --> 37:24.239
- Stay here with us.
- I can make it.

37:24.325 --> 37:26.533
Please, didn't you see
that guy just get eaten before?

37:26.619 --> 37:28.576
Yeah, which is why we need
to get out of the water.

37:28.663 --> 37:30.700
No, if you go by yourself they will get you.

37:30.790 --> 37:32.577
We have to stick together, okay? Come on.

37:32.667 --> 37:35.000
- Josh, go for it.
- What?

37:35.086 --> 37:36.702
You're okay with him just swimming off?

37:36.796 --> 37:38.082
We got to... we got to take this chance.

37:38.173 --> 37:39.334
We have to stick together.

37:40.341 --> 37:42.628
No, come on. Stay with us.

37:43.762 --> 37:45.594
Another one's going to come, okay?

37:49.392 --> 37:51.179
You could've had that, Josh.

37:51.269 --> 37:52.726
The Coast Guard will come.

37:52.812 --> 37:55.099
We can't separate, okay?

38:02.071 --> 38:05.189
<i>A freak wave has capsized a shark dive boat,</i>

38:05.283 --> 38:09.197
<i>throwing everyone overboard</i>
<i>into shark infested waters.</i>

38:09.287 --> 38:11.779
There were a number of
injuries ranging in severity.

38:11.873 --> 38:16.334
And also we can confirm several fatalities.

38:20.423 --> 38:22.961
<i>The rescue effort is continuing</i>

38:23.051 --> 38:25.794
<i>and we have a handful of people</i>
<i>who are not accounted for.</i>

38:29.224 --> 38:31.056
Can you hear that?

38:40.527 --> 38:42.189
This is insane.

38:43.321 --> 38:44.812
What are we doing out here?

38:44.906 --> 38:46.568
You all right?

38:50.954 --> 38:53.412
I can't... I can't swim anymore.

38:56.751 --> 38:58.583
I'm so tired.

38:58.670 --> 39:01.504
You just got to relax. Okay, Megan? Please.

39:01.589 --> 39:05.048
All right? It's the only way
we're going to get through this.

39:05.134 --> 39:07.126
Look, just lie on your back.

39:08.596 --> 39:11.054
It will help you float. Lean back.

39:12.100 --> 39:13.261
Here you go.

39:13.351 --> 39:15.138
I'm going to keep looking
for the helicopters.

39:21.234 --> 39:22.224
What is it?

39:23.236 --> 39:25.068
- What was it, Megan?
- I felt something.

39:25.154 --> 39:26.611
It touched me.

39:33.830 --> 39:35.366
Oh, my God!

39:38.459 --> 39:40.166
Oh, it's a piece of bait.

39:57.061 --> 39:59.474
- Jeff!
- Jeff!

40:00.648 --> 40:02.059
Stay together, guys.

40:02.150 --> 40:05.109
Did you see it? Did you see where it went?

40:05.194 --> 40:06.651
I'm going to go check it out.

40:14.162 --> 40:15.778
It's gone, it's gone.

40:18.374 --> 40:19.990
It's okay, it's okay.

40:21.002 --> 40:22.083
I saw it swim off.

40:26.758 --> 40:27.794
What the hell is that?

40:28.885 --> 40:30.251
What is that?

40:30.345 --> 40:32.086
- Can you see?
- I don't know.

40:32.180 --> 40:35.719
We need to get it. We could float on
that thing, whatever it is.

40:37.477 --> 40:40.345
It's definitely coming this way.

40:42.565 --> 40:43.681
Come on, come on. Swim to it.

40:58.873 --> 41:00.409
Yeah!

41:00.500 --> 41:02.207
High five.

41:03.711 --> 41:05.668
- Thank you.
- Oh, my God.

41:07.006 --> 41:08.838
Oh, my hands.

41:11.719 --> 41:13.210
Frickin' salt.

41:17.642 --> 41:21.306
In an hour or two,
Coast Guard's going to be here,

41:21.396 --> 41:23.809
and this will be just a crazy story.

41:25.817 --> 41:28.605
Just a crazy story.

41:28.695 --> 41:33.151
You're going to be pulling all the chicks,
Josh, telling them about this story.

41:33.241 --> 41:34.448
You know it.

41:34.534 --> 41:37.242
There's no way I'm not using this story.

41:37.328 --> 41:39.536
I'm going to get free beer for life.

41:39.622 --> 41:40.863
- Guys.
- And I'm going to tell

41:40.957 --> 41:42.869
all the girls that you saved us.

41:42.959 --> 41:46.669
Guys, will you...
will you just shut up for a minute?

41:46.754 --> 41:49.212
Just stop joking around, okay?

41:50.299 --> 41:52.382
Megan, we got to stay positive.

41:52.468 --> 41:54.004
Stay positive about what?

41:55.096 --> 41:58.680
Megan, you've got to conserve your energy.

41:58.766 --> 42:02.510
We're going to get through this...
aren't we, Josh?

42:02.603 --> 42:05.016
- Yeah.
- We're gonna get through it.

42:05.106 --> 42:06.768
Fucking hands though are getting eaten up.

42:06.858 --> 42:08.690
Right? Come on, Megan.

42:08.776 --> 42:12.520
You don't have to be all scared all the time.

42:12.613 --> 42:14.570
What are you kidding me?

42:14.657 --> 42:16.649
We're probably being circled by sharks.

42:16.743 --> 42:21.283
Let's talk about what you
wanna do when you get back.

42:21.372 --> 42:24.581
Oh, just, you know, go to McDonald's.

42:25.960 --> 42:27.576
Just eat a burger.

42:27.670 --> 42:29.286
You wanna eat a burger when you get back.

42:29.380 --> 42:30.461
What do you wanna do, Megan?

42:32.175 --> 42:36.294
Megan! What do you wanna
do when you get back?

42:38.473 --> 42:39.634
Let's look at the clouds.

42:41.642 --> 42:43.634
Oh, that's so cold.

42:49.442 --> 42:50.978
- Where is it coming from?
- See it?

42:51.069 --> 42:52.355
It's getting louder.

42:52.445 --> 42:54.277
- I can see it.
- Where?

42:54.363 --> 42:55.695
- Up there.
- Right up there.

42:55.782 --> 42:58.525
- I see it.
- It's like a little white one.

42:58.618 --> 43:01.235
Oh, it's way too high.

43:01.329 --> 43:04.288
It's all right. It's probably just
scouting out the area.

43:04.373 --> 43:06.786
- He'll be back.
- Hey!

43:06.876 --> 43:10.870
- Megan, he's not... he can't see us.
- Megan, Megan.

43:10.963 --> 43:13.205
- Megan, relax.
- Then help me!

43:13.299 --> 43:15.256
- Hello!
- Megan!

43:16.594 --> 43:18.130
Stop laughing at me!

43:18.221 --> 43:21.214
This is not fucking funny, okay?
We need to get rescued, right?

43:21.307 --> 43:22.263
You got to help me.

43:22.350 --> 43:24.433
- We can barely see the... Megan!
- Help!

43:24.519 --> 43:26.761
We can barely see the plane.
They can't see us.

43:26.854 --> 43:28.971
Gosh, just saying relax.

43:29.065 --> 43:31.682
It's okay, Megan. It's all right.

43:32.944 --> 43:34.230
We at least have to try, you know.

43:34.320 --> 43:36.277
Like, do you even want to get rescued?

43:36.364 --> 43:39.778
Yeah, I do. I wanted to
get to the boat, but you said "no".

43:39.867 --> 43:41.324
We can't split up.

43:44.914 --> 43:46.826
Jeff?

43:49.961 --> 43:52.044
What's wrong? Can you say something?

43:54.215 --> 43:55.831
Are you okay?

44:01.305 --> 44:02.637
You okay?

44:05.059 --> 44:06.595
Is it... is it your heart?

44:06.686 --> 44:10.145
- Do you need... Do you need something?
- I'm fine.

44:10.231 --> 44:12.188
- I'm good, I'm good.
- You sure?

44:12.275 --> 44:13.891
Megan, leave him be.

44:16.070 --> 44:17.652
I'm just going to lie on my back.

44:17.738 --> 44:20.856
Okay, we got you. I got you, Jeff. It's okay.

44:36.382 --> 44:37.873
I hope they get here.

44:50.229 --> 44:51.891
Oh, shit.

44:51.981 --> 44:53.597
- What?
- Josh...

44:53.691 --> 44:55.933
See that... heading out there?

44:56.027 --> 44:58.770
Josh, can you zoom in on that?

45:03.242 --> 45:04.699
I'm gonna go for it.

45:04.785 --> 45:05.992
No, Jeff. Jeff, stay here. Come on.

45:06.078 --> 45:08.161
